title: Kiasmos â€“ Looped
description:
Ã“lafur Arnalds and Janus Rasmussen finally release their unique Nordic electronic sounds in album size.

Get the limited edition 12" exclusively on Record Store Day 2015.
Order the album on 2xLP/CD/DL: http://www.erasedtapes.com/store/index/ERATP062
Or order the album DL via iTunes: http://snip.ftpromo.net/kiasmos

After dropping several tracks and performing at select festivals throughout the years, Ã“lafur Arnalds and Janus Rasmussen dedicated the year 2014 to explore the area in-between Ã“lafurâ€™s more acoustic, piano-based solo work and Janusâ€™s synth-heavy electro pop, with their collaborative electronic project Kiasmos.

By focusing solely on their self-titled debut album, Ã“lafur and Janus have been able to combine and further develop their unique sound aesthetics to complete an album driven by their mutual love for electronic music. Made in Ã“lafurâ€™s newly build studio in ReykjavÃ­k, Iceland, a majority of the album was recorded using acoustic instruments next to a variety of synthesisers, drum machines and tape delays. It features a live drummer, string quartet and Ã“lafur performing on the grand piano, producing an ambient, textured sound, which makes it a perfect home listen and equally danceable record. If you listen closely, you can spot them record the thumb piano, finger snapping and even the sound of the metal grinder of a lighter slowly to replace the usual electronic hi-hat sounds, giving the album a far more intimate and unique atmosphere.

â€œWe decided to start almost completely over with this record, so most of the material is written this year with the idea of making a record that can stand as one piece rather than a collection of songs. I am very excited to get a proper record out exploring a different territory than I am used to. I touch a lot on electronic genres in my own music but never have the opportunity to go full out electronic like we do here.â€ â€“ Ã“lafur Arnalds

â€œThe Kiasmos project has been around since 2007, but because of all our other projects we never really got the time to sit down and write all the tracks we always wanted to. So when we early this year finally found the time to sit down and make a full length album there was so much we wanted to try out. The result surprised us a bit, it's deeper and more emotional than we imagined it to be, but that's the beauty of being able to make an album.â€ â€“ Janus Rasmussen

Kiasmos â€“ s/t will be released on Double-Vinyl, CD and Download via Erased Tapes on October 27th, 2014.

title: All That Has Changed
description:
Part of an attempt to create poetry for a mythic post-apocalyptic science fantasy world.

Text:

In the desert, the stars
shine down coldly across
infinity's dark plains

as though there could still be
purpose in this empty
and once glittering place 

the dark sands and cold lights 
of a vaulted midnight 
still stretch to the endless

and all that has changed is 
that you are not here and 
I watch the skies alone

title: Hunted Love | Hannah Macleod
description:
Hannah Macleod is the winner of the most impressive vocalist award of The Song Academy Young Songwriter 2013 Competition.

The Song Academy Young Songwriter Competition is an exciting platform for aspiring young songwriters, giving young people aged 6-18 years the opportunity to have their songs heard by industry professionals, and the chance to release their own single. The competition is open for young people whoâ€™ve been writing songs for years and for those whoâ€™ll be writing their first song. 

The star-studded judging panel, including leading songwriter and producer for Adele, Duffy, Will Young, James Blunt, Joss Stone, Natalie Imbruglia and James Morrison, Eg White, hugely successful songwriter/producer Fraser T Smith responsible for such hit songs as Adeleâ€™s â€œSet Fire to the Rainâ€, James Morrisonâ€™s â€œBroken Stringsâ€, and Taio Cruzâ€™s â€œBreak Your Heartâ€, plus producer for Britney Spears, Kylie Minogue, Leona Lewis and Keane, award winning songwriter and producer, singer-songwriter Amy Studt, First Newsâ€™ editor Nicky Cox, BBC Radio 6 Musicâ€™s Tom Robinson, JLSâ€™s writer Lyn Goddard, world famous songwriter Barry Mason, Apple and iTunes advisor and founder of AWAL Denzyl Feigelson, Youth Musicâ€™s Matt Griffiths, The Mercury Prize nominated singer songwriter Lou Rhodes and Heart Radioâ€™s Jamie Theakston were all hugely impressed with just how high the standard was. 

Eg White "Normally upon listening to the results of a songwriting competition, what comes across is how the competitors are trying to write commercial sounding music or impress with their cleverness or catchiness, but listening to these songs, I just really enjoyed the music, and could actually feel the people behind the songs, which has to be pretty close to the whole point of writing!" 

Amy Studt "I think this is a fantastic way of young talent getting recognised and showcasing some of their work. I was in a songwriting competition when I was 12 and it really boosted my confidence and my belief in what I was doing. The talent this year had been fantastic and I have loved being a part of it. "

Denzyl Feigelson â€œI found the quality of songwriting to be surprisingly creative and quite advanced, yet refreshingly young and vibrant. The general and combined subject matter also gives one an indication of what 6-18 year olds are experiencing in their lives, and also the challenges they are having in today's modern society. I also found some of the musicianship and raw talent to be exceedingly good.  What a wonderful outlet for communicationâ€.

Tom Robinson "It was most impressive to hear young writers singing or rapping about their own lives without any outside input or help from adults. It bodes well for the future of music in this country."

Nicky Cox "Britain makes music that is played all over the world. The standard of the song writing in this competition shows that tradition isn't about to change. The future of British music is in very safe hands.\

title: Tritonal - Anchor (Noisestorm Remix) [OUT NOW]
description:
Stream / Download: https://enhanced.lnk.to/X50R_

Follow us on Spotify: http://enhan.co/EM-Spotify

Label: Enhanced Recordings
Cat. Number: Enhanced200R
Subscribe to Enhanced âœ http://enhan.co/SubscribeEnhanced

Tritonal's 'Anchor' has been widely regarded as one of the biggest vocal-led anthems to hit the Progressive House scene this year - tearing up the airwaves and festival stages around the world since its release on Tritonal's third & final EP in the 'Metamorphic' series. Whilst the infectious vocal from the original is still ringing in every Tritonian's head around the world, we get ready to see in the remix package which features an assortment of six new & equally incredible takes on the original.

Tritonal deliver their own devastating 'Club Mix', which takes on a powerful & driving new guise whilst retaining the original's emotional vocals in a beautifully crafted alternative version. Next up are Italian talents Lush & Simon - a duo who have been enjoying huge success recently. They add gritty undertones, and rumbling, rolling bass with a new wave of euphoric sentiment to the original's lead. While M35 maybe a name that's fairly new, the American producer has quickly set himself out from the crowd with un-ashamed, all-out EDM warfare in his tracks & remixes. His version for 'Anchor' is no different and boasts one of the hardest drops seen in recent times.

17-year old Norwegian Rootkit has been turning heads of late and the youngster completely switches the original upside down and creates a peak-time future house mix, whilst Irish Drum & Bass tastemaker Noisestorm delivers a superbly energetic DnB remix. Rounding off the remix package is LA-based Unlike Pluto. Featuring some brilliantly innovative production prowess, he brings the EP to a close in real style. A more down-beat and chilled out remix compared to the others, but no less impressive, the producer's combination of a variety of styles makes this one of the most exciting remixes we've heard in sometime.

Tritonal's modern anthem 'Anchor' has enjoyed incredible success as an original release, and this forward-thinking remix package delivers the original's thrills all over again.

title: Billy Alex - Graphic Design (Simos Tagias Remix) Master www.AMStudio.pro
description: Abstract Space Records introduces the second track of the two part special titled Graphic Design in it's 32nd release. Both this and the previous release are dedicated to Abstract Space Records' graphic designer, our very own da Vinci of album covers, Michael \"Handsome\" Gaida! Contrasting his first release, Greek artist Billy Alex colors this wondrous soundscape with vivid hues of moody pads and overlays of subtle synthesizer hits against a backdrop of a dark bass in this deep progressive piece. Luciano Scheffer appears for the first time on Abstract Space Records and quickly delves into a dark world of his own with his trademark rhythms of complex, phased out melodies and hypnotic percussion work. Simos Tagias starts out his remix with a vibrant mosaic of hand percussion entangled with bright claps that promises a light and airy house remix before shattering all preconceptions with a hollow, driving bass intoned with an almost didgeridoo-esque drone. Alfonso Muchacho brings his techy, progressive sound to the table in an upbeat remix of sighing pads, dramatic synthesizer hits, and massive bass line over the now familiar rambling lead of the original track.

title: Believe
description:
Hey you guys! So my album Lemonade is now available for your ears! UP is a bold reintroduction and step forward, with guitarists NICK FUELLING and DAVEY GRAHS, bassist MATT DIRITO, drummer CHACHI RIOT and Kakaty at the top of their game. Itâ€™s always a bit clichÃ©, not to mention questionable, when a band says their new album is the best one yet. But in the case of POP EVIL, itâ€™s an absolute fact.

POP EVIL smashes through the odds like a battering ram, weathering the trials and tribulations of paying dues with a steadfast resilience owing much to their blue collar and middle class backgrounds, and building a worldwide audience one fan at a time. As the moniker promises when emblazoned on a CD or radio dial, POP EVIL conjures aggressive riffs and hard charging sing-a-longs with emotional heft and melodic power in equal measure. title: Alessia Cara X G-Eazy - Wild Things (Young Bombs Remix)
description:
Thank you for getting it to #1 on HypeM!!! http://bit.ly/WildThingsHype

Buy on iTunes: smarturl.it/WildThingsRmxs 

The first time Martin heard this song on the radio, he called me (Tristan) up and was like, "you HAVE to hear this new song by Alessia Cara! It has this dope 'ay ay ay ahhh' vocal chant in the chorus!" Right away, we thought about how awesome it would be to remix it. Then about a week later, our manager emailed us the track (without knowing how much we liked it) and asked us if we wanted to take a stab at it. No brainer.

Anyways, we had so much fun making this remix! We made a crazy vocal chop in the drop, I played a little guitar, and it was our first time working with a rap. Hope you guys like it, and if you do, PLEASE give it a heart on HypeM. Thanks!

title: Chuckie \u0026 ChildsPlay - Insane - Traphall EP [DDFR01]
description:
Watch on YouTube: http://dirtydut.ch/INSANE_yt

Continuing the expansion of Dirty Dutch Music, Chuckie finds his stride with this latest effort, Traphall. A brand new 4 Track EP, this collaboration with Childsplay features a bombastic hybrid of trap and classic Dancehall tunes unlike any before it. Traphall is a testament to Chuckieâ€™s vision for Dirty Dutch Music. This incomparable leadership is taking the label into all spectrums of dance music, leaving no stone unturned. Precursing singles, â€œVamonosâ€ and â€œBang!â€, saw the king of Dirty Dutch leave his one-of-a-kind mark within Melbourne Bounce. Chuckieâ€™s highly anticipated follow up came in a larger than life remix of Deadmau5â€™s seminal â€œGhosts â€˜Nâ€™ Stuffâ€. Successfully reworking a groundbreaking classic of such notoriety cannot be understated, as it breathed new life for modern audiences without ever losing the allure of its source material. Traphall is Chuckieâ€™s next step into the dance music stratosphere, unleashing an inimitable fusion between styles of vastly different musical backgrounds from the past and the present. 

Starting the EP off on a perfect foot, Chuckie & Childsplay make sure listeners know that itâ€™s all about the mula by making it rain with â€œMoneyâ€. This track sets the mood with charging bass drum kicks and unexpected synth patterns, literally breaking any preconceived genre boundaries with every passing second. The manic, tribal progression never once lets up, maintaining a peak energy level throughout its entirety. Chuckie and Childsplay embark on this audible journey with bass shattering, epic proportions, tantalizing listeners with whatâ€™s to come. 

Calming the senses with an eerie, yet infectious vibe is Traphallâ€™s next offering,  â€œSensimilliaâ€. Harnessing a smooth, driving riddim thatâ€™s fueled by powerful vocal loops, Chuckie and Childsplay seamlessly infuse reggae with unparalleled results. The gradual buildup mesmerizes before eventually reaching a climax that never feels out of place. Chuckieâ€™s patented Dirty Dutch sound is instantly recognizable, receiving a Dancehall spin that meshes together flawlessly. The second drop is a downtempo variation that introduces elements typically associated with trap. A suitable follow up, Traphallâ€™s sophomore production hits listeners with an unrivaled attack of reggaeton.

Embodying the true feeling of Traphall, â€œInsaneâ€, is led by wickedly powerful vocals, iconic island piano key strokes and intense dance trap breakdowns. This smorgasbord of vastly diverse stylings highlights the underlying challenge of making Traphall a working reality. Chuckie and Childsplay both emanate a clear mastery of these genres, which is already an impressive accolade in itself. Implementing each one in a distinct fashion, while still being able to create an all encompassing final product is nothing short of groundbreaking. A breathtaking reggae anthem one moment and a staccato like trap breakdown the next, â€œInsaneâ€ brings something truly new to the table within a saturated landscape of dance music.

 â€œWickedâ€ is influenced by the timeless, â€œShe is Not My Kindâ€, by Gregory Isaacs. A proper conclusion to the EP, this production reinstates the true spirit of Dancehall for a brand new generation of fans. Rocking out with some serious heart-pounding 808 kicks, while evoking the unparalleled charisma of Dirty Dutch, â€œWickedâ€ is a tribute to everything that has helped shape Chuckie and Childsplay during their illustrious musical careers. Traphall closes out this musical expedition with a track that perfectly evokes the respect, love, knowledge and skill necessary for such a project. An ode to past heroes and new influences alike, this unabashed love letter showcases a bright future in dance music that will never forget its roots.

"The 30th release from Ã˜SCILLATE is here, and itâ€™s from more homegrown Liverpool talent, and the latest Ã˜SCILLATE member, Larmour. Three mind-benders are within the aptly titled EP, Shattered Reality.

First up, Inside Out. A broken beat carries this beauty along, with rising synths pads, and hypnotic melodies throughout. The dark underbelly of this track gives it some serious weight - a perfect tune for building tension and keeping classy.

The title track speaks for itself. Huge sounds in this one. The percussion runs tight in, the flecks of acid get beneath your skin, and the atmospheres build into huge dramatic drops.

title: Spanish Train - Chris de Burgh
description:
Album : Spanish Train and Other Stories
Live Performance


<u>Lyrics</u>
There's a Spanish train that runs between
Guadalquivir and old Saville,
And at dead of night the whistle blows,
and people hear she's running still...

And then they hush their children back to sleep,
Lock the doors, upstairs they creep,
For it is said that the souls of the dead
Fill that train ten thousand deep!!

Well a railwayman lay dying with his people by his side,
His family were crying, knelt in prayer before he died,
But above his bed just a-waiting for the dead,
Was the Devil with a twinkle in his eye,
"Well God's not around and look what I've found,
this one's mine!!"

Just then the Lord himself appeared in a blinding flash of light,
And shouted at the Devil, "Get thee hence to endless night!!"
But the Devil just grinned and said "I may have sinned,
But there's no need to push me around,
I got him first so you can do your worst,
He's going underground!!"

"But I think I'll give you one more chance",
said the Devil with a smile,
"So throw away that stupid lance,
It's really not your style",
"Joker is the name, Poker is the game,
we'll play right here on this bed,
And then we'll bet for the biggest stakes yet,
the souls of the dead!!"

And I said "Look out, Lord, He's going to win,
The sun is down and the night is riding in,
That train is dead on time, many souls are on the line,
Oh Lord, He's going to win!.."

Well the railwayman he cut the cards
And he dealt them each a hand of five,
And for the Lord he was praying hard
Or that train he'd have to drive...
Well the Devil he had three aces and a king,
And the Lord, he was running for a straight,
He had the queen and the knave and nine and ten of spades,
All he needed was the eight...

And then the Lord he called for one more card,
But he drew the diamond eight,
And the Devil said to the son of God,
"I believe you've got it straight,
So deal me one for the time has come
To see who'll be the king of this place,
But as he spoke, from beneath his cloak,
He slipped another ace...

Ten thousand souls was the opening bid,
And it soon went up to fifty-nine,
But the Lord didn't see what the Devil did,
And he said "that suits me fine",
"I'll raise you high to a hundred and five,
And forever put an end to your sins",
But the Devil let out a mighty shout, "My hand wins!!"

And I said "Lord, oh Lord, don't let him win,
The sun is down and the night is riding in,
That train is dead on time, many souls are on the line,
Oh Lord, don't let him win..."

Well that Spanish train still runs between,
Guadalquivir and old Saville,
And at dead of night the whistle blows,
And people fear she's running still...
And far away in some recess
The Lord and the Devil are now playing chess,
The Devil still cheats and wins more souls,
And as for the Lord, well, he's just doing his best...

And I said "Lord, oh Lord, you've got to win,
The sun is down and the night is riding in,
That train is still on time, oh my soul is on the line,
Oh Lord, you've got to win..."

title: Mick Harvey - Bonnie \u0026 Clyde
description:
'Bonnie & Clyde' - featuring Anita Lane, Warren Ellis and Bertrand Burgalat - is taken from the reissued double CD collection of Mick Harvey's two Serge Gainsbourg albums, Intoxicated Man and Pink Elephants, released on Mute on 7 April 2014 (6 May in the US).Order it here: Double CD: http://smarturl.it/harveyman14
iTunes: http://smarturl.it/digiharveyman14
Google Play: bit.ly/1ioCILu

Intoxicated Man (1995) and Pink Elephants (1997) are Mick Harveyâ€™s interpretations of the songs of legendary singer, songwriter and poet Serge Gainsbourg and are the first major works translating Gainsbourgâ€™s infuential work from French to English. The double CD collection will include two unreleased tracks, Dr Jeckyll and Run From Happiness.

The vocal parts originally sung by Gainsbourgâ€™s muses Jane Birkin, Brigitte Bardot and daughter Charlotte Gainsbourg are here sung by long time collaborator Anita Lane â€“ other guests on the albums include Nick Cave and David McClymont.

Mick Harvey Website: http://www.mickharvey.com/
Mute: www.mute.com

title: Wildlife! - Drop It ft. Rapha
description:
For true Enchufada fans, the Swiss producer and DJ Wildlife! should need no introduction by now. After contributing the fiery Metazoa for our Hard Ass Session EP series back in 2010, he recently teamed up with young dancehall producer Rapha on the Upper Cuts free download series, delivering the UK Funky inspired dancefloor filler PC Riddim. As it turns out, this was only the beginning for this fruitful collaboration on Enchufada. 

Enter the steaming hot 'Boiler EP', a three-track collection including the aforementioned PC Riddim alongside two new fresh cuts - the titular Boiler Riddim and Drop It. While PC Riddim and Boiler Riddim take inspiration from the early UK Funky scene, providing playful looping synths, heavy bassline pressure and dancefloor-focused percussion, Drop It draws heavily from the producers' dancehall background, flipping classic dancehall patterns into a futuristic bashment vibe. Following his recently-released 'Roxy Reboot' album, where classic punk tracks are given the reggae treatment and vice-versa, Wildlife! proves once again just how much that small Caribbean island keeps offering to contemporary electronic music. 

www.enchufada.com
www.itswildlife.com
